{
  "stem": "12447.2",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So to me, it was a shock because I never knew what means being thrown out of a house, or being beaten up.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And this kind of mattered to me.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "A policeman was the man that really protected the people.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But over there, the way they described that, the, the police came, and they threw them out.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So it was kind of-- I couldn't, couldn't quite understand what was really going on.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But I knew that Hitler-- the name Hitler wasn't too kind to Jews and, and seemed like something was cooking, something-- like, people would be scared of Germans, in particular.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And coming-- like my sister, when she came back afterwards, and telling that there might be a war with Germany-- so it kind of-- I was a, a little bit more aware of what was going on.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we were frightened of this situation.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I was frightened of this situation as a child.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I remember my father came once from work-- I don't know if it was work, or he had a meeting from this-- he belonged to the Bund, from the Jewish workers organization.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he came, and he was quite beaten up.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he had a broken nose and telling us that some of the hooligans, hooligans beat him up because he was a Jew.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So all that, the situation was getting tense and insecure for Jews to go out in the evening or trying to be more indoors and not to-- and they would kind of warn me not to run around too much and stay, more or less, near the house, things like that.",
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So that was kind of leading up to the war, which I didn't understand what, what actually war meant.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
